<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1898-06-13T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1898-06-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="329" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d329">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Powell</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Day</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Port au Prince, Haiti</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1898-06-13"><hi rend="italic">June
                                        13, 1898</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 298.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I respectfully transmit draft in favor of
                            Secretary of State on Messrs. Lyon &amp; Co. for $4,950.50 received by
                            me from the Haitian Government as the first payment on the Campbell
                            claim.</p>
                        <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">W. F. Powell.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>